What to change: keep N1’s legacy rule (0.9 GiB/vCPU), but set 2 GiB/vCPU for modern HIGHCPU (N4/N4A/C4/C4D etc.). This matches Google’s published machine family ratios and prevents unexpected RAM mismatches in the UI for new series.

